title: Omloop Ohop
description: Omloop Ohop is a Belgian Style Kermesse race.  Elite Women will start at 11am.  Senior Men and Masters will start at 1am.  Senior and Masters Men will be scored seperately.
course: 2 mile Ohop circuit: 1 mile pavement and 1 mile cobblestone-like hard-pack dirt. There is a short climb at 300 meters into the dirt section. 700x25c puncture resistant tires and strong wheels are recommended; There are 3 wheel pits on the course.
registration: ields are limited to 50 riders per race due to unique course. Pre-registration (http://axleyusa.com/store/page8.html) is strongly encouraged. Registration opens at 9am and closes 20 minutes prior to race.
notes: WSBA numbers will be used and they will go on your left side. Day-of licenses will be available for Cat 4/5 riders only. UCSF license is required.
directions: Approximately 1 hour and 45 minutes from Seattle. Take I-5 to exit #127. Take exit #127 onto WA-512 EAST toward PUYALLUP/S TACOMA WAY - go 2.4 miles. Take the PACIFIC AVE exit toward SPANAWAY/PARKLAND - go 0.3 miles. Turn R on PACIFIC AVE S [WA-7] - go 5.1 miles. Bear L to follow WA-7 SOUTH - go 18 miles to Mashel Prairie Rd. Take R (there will be a sign). Registration will be on right.

title: Baddlands Cooper Jones Frozen Flatlands Omnium

NWHP Collegiate Challenge Cup
description: 1st annual Blue Mtn. Challenge Cup. This event is open to collegiate riders from the Northwest Collegiate Conference. It is held in the foothills of the Blue Mountains. It is the intent of the organizing committee to develop this event into the premier collegiate cycling event in the Northwest.
course: The RR course is held on rolling country roads. It is approximatly a 14 mile loop course. The Team Time Trial is an out and back route is a slight uphill grade to flat course going out, and a slight downhill grade to the finish. The criterium is a very fast course on the beautiful campus of Walla Walla University, in downtown College Place WA. It features wide corners, and a slight climb ont he back side of the square course.
registration: For registration information contact Blue Mountain Challenge Cup at bmchallengecup@charter.net
directions: Race directions will be posted on the Northwest Collegiate Conference list serve. If you need directions sooner or clarification, please contact bmchallengecup@charter.net

title: Ravensdale Cumberland Road Race
course: Rolling course in SE King County.  Pavement is fair to very good.  One short, 0.15 mile, steep 20%, hill.  Course map available at www.vision4corners.com
registration: Online registration through 5/31/07 at Active.com (transaction fee applies) or mail check and completed USA Cycling Release Form (WSBA number in upper right) by 5/25/07 to:  Michael Kopp, PO Box 873, Maple Valley, WA  98038.  Checks payable to 4 Corners Cycling-Michael Kopp.  Preregistration is $ 25.  Day of race registration is $ 30.
notes: See www.vision4corners.com for complete race notes
directions: Parking and Race Staging is at King County Ravensdale Park just outside Maple Valley.  From WA SR 169 (exit #4 off I-405) go east on Kent Kangley Rd approximately 2 miles to the park entrance on the south.
